.TH "i915_memcpy_from_wc" 9 "i915_memcpy_from_wc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_memcpy_from_wc \- perform an accelerated *aligned* read from WC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" i915_memcpy_from_wc
.BI "(void *dst "  ","
.BI "const void *src "  ","
.BI "unsigned long len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
destination pointer
.IP "src" 12
source pointer
.IP "len" 12
how many bytes to copy
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
i915_memcpy_from_wc copies \fIlen\fP bytes from \fIsrc\fP to \fIdst\fP using
non-temporal instructions where available. Note that all arguments
(\fIsrc\fP, \fIdst\fP) must be aligned to 16 bytes and \fIlen\fP must be a multiple
of 16.

To test whether accelerated reads from WC are supported, use
i915_memcpy_from_wc(NULL, NULL, 0);

Returns true if the copy was successful, false if the preconditions
are not met.
